public class Date
extends Date

Provides a consistent way to format a Date for display in JFC components. It is expected that a Date will normally be displayed using toString() which typically occurs in JFC TableModel-type components. You can modify the way all Dates are displayed by using setFormat(). By default, a java.text.DateFormat is used that has been created using DateFormat.getDateTimeInstance(MEDIUM,MEDIUM)
